== General Principles for RKC

#Natural bidding takes priority over asking for key-cards.#

_I.e.,_{thinsp} we don't sacrifice useful natural bids for uncommon
situations such as asking for key-cards without first agreeing trump.
This is based on frequency and usefuless which are overwhelmingly in favour
natural bids.

=== Set trumps first

If it's possible to set a suit as trump with an unambiguous below-game
forcing-bid, then that route must be taken to ask for key-cards in
that suit.

[%autowidth,cols="3*^,<",grid="none"]
|===
| 1H |  1S   | |
| 2H |  ?    | |
|    |  2NT  | | natural inv.
|    |  3H   | | inv.
|    |  3S   | | forcing, at most a one-loser suit
|    | !4C!  | | splinter [nobr]##(#could be fake#)##
|    |  4H   | | to play
|    |  4S   | | to play
|    |  4NT  | | natural inv.
           [nobr]#(forcing-2NT unavailable)#
|===

Responder can set hearts as trump unambiguously with a splinter, which
could possibly be fake, so cannot ask for KC this round.

=== When we cannot set trumps first

If we get to the 3-level and do not have an unambiguous way to set
trump, then kickback will be ON, provided that we have
another way to make a natural bid in the suit of the KC ask.

.Examples
