=== Three-level non-agreement

The general principle is that for 4m to be minorwood, we must first
explicitely agree the minor-suit, or set it as trumps with a transfer
after a notrump opening.

So when opener or responder bids a minor at the 3-level, a raise to 4m
is just forward going (forcing).

The KC-asking bid is #a jump to a suit-bid below 4NT#.
It is the cheapest of: +
@ unbid-suit
@ fourth suit
@ opener's 2nd-suit
@ responder's 2nd-suit

